reviewText: Quite frankly, this is an amateurish quickly made documentary meant to make a fast buck from Susan Boyle's fame.  If you have an all-region DVD player, get the British "Susan Boyle Story" from the BBC which you can get for about $15.00 on Ebay.  It's much better done.JF

reviewText: If you like Susan Boyle's voice and if you've wondered where she's been all this time, this book is for you.  It's full of pictures and information about her childhood, her breakdown and why she, like her voice,  is a fragile gift.I love her songs, talent, and her courage to not only "sing her heart out", but to cross those divides that the show biz world places you into so that THEY can package your talent.  She has the talent, the voice and the grace to sing across the genres of the music world.I say sing on Susan and give us more across those song barriers!!  The world wants to hear and see you, and only you can do it!!

reviewText: A disappointing pastiche of old videos and poor-quality audio.  I was hoping for more video of Susan singing.  All in all, an amateurish result.  However, since I am a fan of Susan, I would recommend other fans buying the DVD.  She is going to become extremely famous one day and this, albeit inferior, DVD will become a collector's item.  Vive Susan!
